</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A8D0653DFE49FE2F5889FB65FE6367F5" pageId="388" pageNumber="389" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="E07536B6FE49FE2F5889FB65FC60675B" blockId="388.[151,1437,967,1570]" pageId="388" pageNumber="389">
REMARKS: 
<bibRefCitation id="845B4B47FE49FE2F5914FB65FDB5647B" author="Rondani, C." box="[266,518,1256,1283]" pageId="388" pageNumber="389" refId="ref368338" refString="Rondani, C. (1856) Dipterologiae italicae prodromus. Vol: I. Genera italica ordinis dipterorum ordinatim disposita et distincta et in familias et stirpes aggregata. A. Stocchi, Parmae [= Parma], 226 pp. + [2] pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 8160" type="book" year="1856">Rondani’s (1856: 190)</bibRefCitation>
key for the genus 
<emphasis id="D2BEEAA4FE49FE2F5ACBFB64FC93647B" box="[725,800,1257,1282]" italics="true" pageId="388" pageNumber="389">Bertea</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="845B4B47FE49FE2F5B38FB65FC78647A" author="Rondani, C." box="[806,971,1256,1283]" pageId="388" pageNumber="389" refId="ref368338" refString="Rondani, C. (1856) Dipterologiae italicae prodromus. Vol: I. Genera italica ordinis dipterorum ordinatim disposita et distincta et in familias et stirpes aggregata. A. Stocchi, Parmae [= Parma], 226 pp. + [2] pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 8160" type="book" year="1856">Rondani, 1856</bibRefCitation>
lists 
<taxonomicName id="27CA4D35FE49FE2F5C18FB64FB74647B" box="[1030,1223,1256,1282]" class="Insecta" family="Tachinidae" genus="Bertea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="388" pageNumber="389" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subaptera">
<emphasis id="D2BEEAA4FE49FE2F5C18FB64FB74647B" box="[1030,1223,1256,1282]" italics="true" pageId="388" pageNumber="389">Bertea subaptera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as its type species, but he did not provide a detailed description, type locality, 
<taxonomicName id="27CA4D35FE49FE2F5B77FA81FC0C645F" box="[873,959,1292,1318]" family="Number" pageId="388" pageNumber="26" rank="family">number</taxonomicName>
or sex of the specimens. In his redescription, 
<bibRefCitation id="845B4B47FE49FE2F591FFABDFE596432" author="Rondani, C." box="[257,490,1328,1355]" pageId="388" pageNumber="389" pagination="1859 - 60" refId="ref368586" refString="Rondani, C. (1860 a) Nota octava ad inserviendum dipterologiae italicae de genere Bertea Rndn. Atti della Societa Italiana di Scienze Naturali, 2 [1859 - 60], 56 - 57, pl. II." type="journal article" year="1860">Rondani (1860a: 57)</bibRefCitation>
specified having just the male sex: “ 
<emphasis id="D2BEEAA4FE49FE2F5B95FABDFBAC6433" box="[907,1055,1328,1354]" italics="true" pageId="388" pageNumber="389">semel marem</emphasis>
[the male once]” collected by Dr. Bertè. 
<bibRefCitation id="845B4B47FE49FE2F590CFAD9FE596416" author="Bezzi, M." box="[274,490,1364,1391]" pageId="388" pageNumber="389" pagination="511 - 526" refId="ref345865" refString="Bezzi, M. (1900 b) Sulla presenza del genere Chionea Dalman in Italia, e la riduzione delle ali nei ditteri. Rendiconti dell'Istituto Lombardo di Scienze e Lettere, Series 2, 33, 511 - 526." type="journal article" year="1900">Bezzi (1900b: 517)</bibRefCitation>
reported the MZUF 
<typeStatus id="3F718814FE49FE2F5ACDFAD9FC866417" box="[723,821,1364,1390]" pageId="388" pageNumber="389">holotype</typeStatus>
as being damaged and unrecognizable, but definitely a dipteran belonging to the family “ 
<taxonomicName id="27CA4D35FE49FE2F5A23FAF5FD4364EB" baseAuthorityName="Evenhuis &amp; Pape" baseAuthorityYear="2020" box="[573,752,1400,1426]" class="Insecta" family="Mycetophilidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="388" pageNumber="389" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Mycetophilidae</taxonomicName>
(Subfam. 
<taxonomicName id="27CA4D35FE49FE2F5B7AFAF5FC6064EA" authorityName="Enderlein" authorityYear="1911" box="[868,979,1400,1427]" class="Insecta" family="Sciaridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="388" pageNumber="389" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Sciarinae">Sciarinae</taxonomicName>
)”, currently the family 
<taxonomicName id="27CA4D35FE49FE2F5CCDFAF5FA8C64EB" authorityName="Billberg" authorityYear="1820" box="[1235,1343,1400,1426]" class="Insecta" family="Sciaridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="388" pageNumber="389" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Sciaridae</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="845B4B47FE49FE2F5D56FAF5FE7164CE" author="Menzel, F. &amp; Mohrig, W." pageId="388" pageNumber="389" pagination="1 - 761" refId="ref359551" refString="Menzel, F. &amp; Mohrig, W. (2000) Revision der palaarktischen Trauermucken (Diptera: Sciaridae). Studia Dipterologica, Supplement, 6, 1 - 761." type="journal article" year="2000">Menzel &amp; Mohrig (2000: 601)</bibRefCitation>
claimed that it is a 
<taxonomicName id="27CA4D35FE49FE2F5A83FA11FC8B64CF" box="[669,824,1436,1462]" class="Insecta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="388" pageNumber="389" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Hymenoptera</taxonomicName>
, and 
<bibRefCitation id="845B4B47FE49FE2F5B6DFA11FB3C64CF" author="O'Hara, J. E. &amp; Cerretti, P. &amp; Pape, T. &amp; Evenhuis, N. L." box="[883,1167,1436,1462]" pageId="388" pageNumber="389" pagination="1 - 268" refId="ref361577" refString="O'Hara, J. E., Cerretti, P., Pape, T. &amp; Evenhuis, N. L. (2011) Nomenclatural studies toward a world list of Diptera genus-group names. Part II: Camillo Rondani. Zootaxa, 3141, 1 - 268. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3141.1.1" type="journal article" year="2011">
O’Hara 
<emphasis id="D2BEEAA4FE49FE2F5BD0FA10FBB564CF" box="[974,1030,1436,1462]" italics="true" pageId="388" pageNumber="389">et al.</emphasis>
(2011: 192)
</bibRefCitation>
followed in treating the genus 
<emphasis id="D2BEEAA4FE49FE2F590FFA4CFEEF64A3" box="[273,348,1473,1498]" italics="true" pageId="388" pageNumber="389">Bertea</emphasis>
in 
<taxonomicName id="27CA4D35FE49FE2F599DFA4DFE6864A3" box="[387,475,1472,1498]" class="Insecta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="388" pageNumber="389" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Diptera</taxonomicName>
. The MZUF 
<typeStatus id="3F718814FE49FE2F5A6EFA4DFD6164A3" box="[624,722,1472,1498]" pageId="388" pageNumber="389">holotype</typeStatus>
is indeed very damaged and, except for part of the thorax and one leg, covered with mold, but it is nonetheless clearly a dipteran. 
<bibRefCitation id="845B4B47FE49FE2F5BAAFA69FB286486" author="Rondani, C." box="[948,1179,1508,1535]" pageId="388" pageNumber="389" pagination="1859 - 60" refId="ref368586" refString="Rondani, C. (1860 a) Nota octava ad inserviendum dipterologiae italicae de genere Bertea Rndn. Atti della Societa Italiana di Scienze Naturali, 2 [1859 - 60], 56 - 57, pl. II." type="journal article" year="1860">Rondani (1860a: 57)</bibRefCitation>
specified that the forewings are reduced and only slightly longer than the halteres (
<figureCitation id="78F12A33FE49FE2F5B6CF985FC74675B" box="[882,967,1544,1570]" captionStart="FIGURE 30" captionStartId="389.[151,250,1086,1110]" captionText="FIGURE 30. Bertea subaptera Rondani, 1856." pageId="388" pageNumber="389">Fig. 30</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
